  "returns": "mindspore.ops.remaindermindspore.ops.remainder(input,other)[source]Compute the remainder of division for the input tensor element-wise.Support implicit type conversion and type promotion.remainder(input,other)==input-input.div(other,rounding_mode=\"floor\")*otherWarningWhen the elements of input exceed 2048, there might be accuracy problems.The calculation results of this operator on Ascend and CPU might be inconsistent.If shape is expressed as (D1,D2… ,Dn), then D1*D2… *DN<=1000000,n<=8.Parametersinput(Union[Tensor,numbers.Number,bool]) – The first input.other(Union[Tensor,numbers.Number,bool]) – The second input.ReturnsTensorSupported Platforms:AscendGPUCPUExamples>>>importmindspore>>># case 1: The shape of two inputs are different>>>x=mindspore.tensor([-4.0,5.0,6.0],mindspore.float16)>>>y=mindspore.tensor([3.0],mindspore.float16)>>>output=mindspore.ops.remainder(x,y)>>>print(output)[2. 2. 0.]>>># case 2: The shape of two inputs are the same>>>x=mindspore.tensor([-4.0,5.0,6.0],mindspore.float16)>>>y=mindspore.tensor([3.0,2.0,3.0],mindspore.float16)>>>output=mindspore.ops.remainder(x,y)>>>print(output)[2. 1. 0.]",
